comment: Pierce (WAS) makes incidental contact with Vasquez (TOR) that does not affect his shot attempt.
Pierce (WAS) does not affect DeRozan's (TOR) RSBQ on the drive to the basket.
Gortat (WAS) jumps vertically and maintains legal guarding position as he defends DeRozan's (TOR) driving layup attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Gooden (WAS) was overturned and Washington was awarded possession.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Vasquez (TOR) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Vasquez (TOR) legally contests Beal's (WAS) jumpshot.
Vasquez (TOR) and Beal (WAS) make incidental contact as Vasquez comes up the court.
Porter (WAS) and Ross (TOR) make incidental contact with one another as Porter defends the alley-oop.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined there were 00:00.4 seconds remaining on the game clock when Toronto was awarded a timeout.
Johnson (TOR) and Nene (WAS) briefly engage away from the ball.
Johnson (TOR) sets the screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Williams (TOR) initiates contact with Wall (WAS) who maintains legal guarding position as he contests the running floater.
Wall (WAS) initiates contact with Johnson (TOR) who maintains legal guarding position as he contests the driving layup attempt.
Nene (WAS) legally obtains the rebound. Contact prior to gaining possession is incidental.
DeRozan (TOR) makes contact with Nene's (WAS) arm and the contact affects his layup attempt.
Nene (WAS) maintains legal guarding with a bent forearm as Johnson (TOR) loses the ball as he rises up for the shot attempt in the lane.
Johnson (TOR) grabs Nene's (WAS) shoulder and affects his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Williams (TOR) makes contact with Porter's (WAS) head as the two jump for the rebound.
Johnson (TOR) sets the screen on Porter (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Vasquez (TOR) makes body to body contact with Beal (WAS) that affects his ability to drive on the baseline.
A 24 Second violation should be called as the ball is still loose when the shot clock expires.

Pierce (WAS) grabs Vasquez (TOR) to foul. The IR review determined that, while Pierce came to Vasquez from the side, he could have obtained a position between the ball and the basket had the play continued and therefore the foul was not a clear path foul.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined that the foul committed by Pierce (WAS) did not meet the criteria for a clear path foul.

Pierce (WAS) jumps vertically to defend Johnson's (TOR) layup, but then lowers his arms. If his arms had come down and no contact made, the play would have been legal. Angle above the rim shows contact and therefore the foul should have been called.
Johnson (TOR) makes contact with Wall (WAS) to commit the take foul after being beaten off the dribble but no foul is called.

Pierce (WAS) makes contact with the inbounds pass in the frontcourt prior to gaining possession in the backcourt. Backcourt rules allow for the ball to be thrown into the backcourt on an inbound during the last two minutes of the game.
Vasquez (TOR) commits a take foul on Beal (WAS).
DeRozan (TOR) commits a take foul on Pierce (WAS).
